Got a birthday party, rehearsal dinner, corporate or other event coming up? We're a great option for your gathering! Inquire today and let us know how we can make your special occasion perfect! Book your party × Did you know we do catering? Whatever your occasion, however big or small, we have the perfect options to choose from. Cater your birthday party, holiday party, corporate events, wedding festivities and more! Catering Packages WELCOME TO Leyla Leyla is Charleston's premier family-owned Lebanese restaurant serving authentic Lebanese dishes in an elegant modern setting and a sophisticated atmosphere. Our extensive Middle Eastern menu offers shareable plates and a communal dining experience. With an extensive Wine and Cocktail list to choose from, you are sure to find the right pairing for your dish. our menu RESERVATIONS accommodate all your needs Whether you're celebrating a special occasion or just looking for a delicious meal, we have the perfect table for you. Book your Leyla Fine Lebanese Cuisine reservation on Resy ORDER ONLINE from the comfort of your home Our restaurant now offers the convenience of online ordering for pick-up or delivery, no need to call or wait in line. order now slideshow start stop playing Slide 1 content Slide 2 content previous slide next slide Exceptional Dining Experience Our Menu Drinks To Complement Your Meal Our Drinks GROUPS & PARTIES customizable party packages With flexible private party space and exceptional cuisine, your guests are sure to have a memorable and enjoyable experience. We can accommodate groups of any size. Inquire Today about a private party catering elevate your event Our catering team is ready to serve you. With years of experience, we're dedicated to making your event a success. inquire now about catering Reviews Start stop reviews carousel Review by - google Aleah G: five star review by Seriously the best Lebanese food I've had in so so long!! Everything, EVERYTHING is homemade. Leyla's cooking is absolutely incredible and she uses the best quality ingredients you could find. I can't wait to come back! A true Charleston gem. Review by - google Denise K: five star review by Wow! We are of Lebanese descent and the food was just as delicious as our grandmothers!! Some dishes were even better! One of the best meals I've ever had! The owner was so attentive and our server was wonderful! Can't wait to go back! Favorite dishes: the grape leaves, lamb shank, moussaka, baklava and pistachio ice cream! Review by - google Blair: five star review by We went here for a Christmas Day lunch and it was delicious! Some of the best hummus I've ever had. My drink was super good and everyone was very kind. We would love to come back and try their standard menu. Review by - google Garrett R: five star review by Easily the tastiest food I've had in South Carolina. A friend and I went in to snack on some falafel and hummus at the bar and loved it so much that we had to go for lunch the next day! This is an absolute must if you're living in Charleston or only visiting. Even if you're full, try the osmalieh for dessert. It's light and the pistachio ice cream is homemade. Review by - google Nanani A: five star review by The meal made my tummy and heart extremely happy. It's like having a home cooked meal that you can taste the joy and all the love in each bite!
